1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:26,428
Psalm 141. LORD, I cry unto thee: make haste unto me; give ear unto my voice, when I cry unto thee. Let my prayer be set forth before thee as incense; and the lifting up of my hands as the evening sacrifice. Set a watch, O LORD, before my mouth; keep the door of my lips.

2
00:00:26,808 --> 00:00:36,722
Incline not my heart to any evil thing, to practise wicked works with men that work iniquity: and let me not eat of their dainties.

3
00:00:37,102 --> 00:00:58,465
Let the righteous smite me; it shall be a kindness: and let him reprove me; it shall be an excellent oil, which shall not break my head: for yet my prayer also shall be in their calamities. When their judges are overthrown in stony places, they shall hear my words; for they are sweet.

4
00:00:58,845 --> 00:01:20,963
Our bones are scattered at the grave’s mouth, as when one cutteth and cleaveth wood upon the earth. But mine eyes are unto thee, O GOD the Lord: in thee is my trust; leave not my soul destitute. Keep me from the snares which they have laid for me, and the gins of the workers of iniquity.

5
00:01:21,343 --> 00:01:27,189
Let the wicked fall into their own nets, whilst that I withal escape.

